data.text:
I'm trying to remember a rather funny movie I saw perhaps a decade or more ago on British TV - I only recall a few details:

You follow a small group - one woman, two men - on a sort of interstellar heavy goods vehicle; they are really not very sophisticated.

They crash-land on the M25 motorway (around London) and take out several bridges.

It is observed by a couple of police officers in a traffic patrol, who report the incident much like they would report an ordinary traffic accident.

I haven't been able to think of the right combination of words to find it - any ideas?
